In this statement, President Obama addresses the attacks that took place in Paris. He condemns the attempt to terrorize innocent civilians and emphasizes that this is not just an attack on Paris or France, but an attack on all of humanity and the universal values we share. The President expresses solidarity with France and offers whatever assistance they may need. He highlights the enduring values of liberty, equality, and fraternity that both the French and American people cherish. The President pledges to work with France and other nations to bring the terrorists to justice and combat any terrorist networks that threaten the safety of the American people. He expresses his condolences to the families of the victims and offers support to the wounded. The President refrains from speculating on who is responsible for the attacks and assures that accurate information will be provided to the press as it becomes available.